Money market rates rates showed a harderedge after news U.K. Chancellor of the Exchequer Nigel Lawsonhas set a target for the pound against the mark and dollar, tobe maintained by a mixture of interest rates and interventionin the foreign exchange markets.    Dealers said the market was surprised by the Chancellor'sdisclosure of sterling target rates, around 2.90 marks and 1.60dlrs, and nervous over the implications for domestic interestrates, further reducing the propects for a near term cut inU.K. Bank base rates. The key three months interbank sterlingrate gained 1/16 point at 10 9-7/8 pct.    The pound opened three basis points lower at 71.3 in tradeweighted terms, at around 1.59 dlrs and 2.91 marks. REUTER&#3;